g/resource/Walter_Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Benjamin\"}, {\"begin\": 796, \"end\": 806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999528649834, \"rank\": 4.713483049163867e-08, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 879, \"end\": 896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wayde van Niekerk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wayde_van_Niekerk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richardson's time of 20.16 seconds met the Olympic qualifying standard, setting the stage for an exciting showdown in Paris.\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 1023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999528649834, \"rank\": 4.713483049163867e-08, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 1017, \"end\": 1022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3247781613196434e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Van Niekerk, who had already qualified for the Olympics in the 400m, finished second in 20.31 seconds.\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1126, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's 100m final also featured a rising star in 18-year-old Bayanda Walaza, who finished second behind seasoned campaigner Akani Simbine.\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1255, \"end\": 1268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walaza's time of 10.27 seconds highlighted his immense potential and marked him as one to watch in the coming years.\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1387, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Simbine, who had already met the Olympic qualifying standard, won the race in 10.01 seconds.\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1480, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The championships saw several athletes secure their spots in Paris in the middle-distance events.\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1543, \"end\": 1548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3247781613196434e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lythe Pillay and Zakithi Nene both dipped under the 45-second mark in the 400m final, with Pillay taking the title in an impressive 44.31 seconds.\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1605, \"end\": 1609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\", \"score\": 0.9999999973997546, \"rank\": 2.6002050393031006e-09, \"text\": \"Nene\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nene, who had already qualified for the Olympics earlier in the season, finished second in 44.80 seconds.In the women's 400m hurdles, Zen\\u00e9y Geldenhuys and Rogail Joseph also met the Olympic qualifying standard.\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1728, \"end\": 1732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\", \"score\": 0.9999999973997546, \"rank\": 2.6002050393031006e-09, \"text\": \"Nene\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\"}, {\"begin\": 1890, \"end\": 1896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"score\": 0.9968216300545334, \"rank\": 0.0031389171761256962, \"text\": \"Joseph\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Geldenhuys took the title in 54.72 seconds, with Joseph close behind in 54.84 seconds, just inside the qualifying mark of 54.85 seconds.\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 2076, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1989, \"end\": 1995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"score\": 0.9968216300545334, \"rank\": 0.0031389171761256962, \"text\": \"Joseph\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Africa's relay teams demonstrated their potential, with Athletics South Africa (ASA) committing to intensive preparation ahead of major international competitions.\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2078, \"end\": 2090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.952386615201428e-15, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 2140, \"end\": 2162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Athletics South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid